						               													<description>You are in Nevada, the year is 1895. Rumors of foul play in the mining town of Silver Creek have led the local marshall to hire you to investigate. With the amount of money available in town, and with the remote location of the town, you would hardly be surprised that something is afoot. But you have little to go on, save the accidental drowning death of a local manager, and the word that witnesses are missing...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sunset at Silver Creek is a complete programmed adventure set in the American West for solitaire or group play. The game includes an adventure booklet, game rules and playing pieces used to resolve the gun fights fought on the game map (also included).  It is the second in the Legends of the Untamed West series which uses a similar game system to Dark City Games' Legends of the Ancient World, which is based on the Fantasy Trip game system.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
